Editor’s note: Watch the live stream above, on DStv 403 or DStv Now PARLIAMENT - Eskom will present its budget review before Parliament on Wednesday. It will appear before the Public Enterprises Portfolio Committee, which is also looking into allegations of state capture at the power utility. The evidence to date has been damning. On Tuesday Eskom Board Spokesperson, Khulani Qoma, said the parastatal oozes dangerous corporate arrogance and top executives are associated with the Guptas. He had the harshest words for Public Enterprises Minister Lynne Brown, who he said was an atrocious minister, captured by the Guptas. Brown later released a statement describing the inquiry as a ‘kangaroo court’ and reiterated that she doesn’t take instructions from anybody. eNCA